! Installation

First you need a Pharo 6.1 image, if you don't have it you can create a new one.
Open Iceberg and clone Steam's github repository.

url : https://github.com/guillep/steam.git

repository : src

+Load Steam's Github repository with Iceberg>file://figures/iceberg.png|label=iceberg+

Now you have to install the baseline of steam.
It will download all needed packages.
+Steam installation with Monticello>file://figures/monticello.png|width=100|label=monticello+


If Icebarg gives you the choice between load existing or incoming version you can choose the first one if the version is greater (higher).
It will take few minutes (usually aroud 4 or 5 min).


Ok that's it ! All you'll need is here, now you can go to the *Initialization>http://www.google.fr* part.

*Initialization>file://initialization.pillar*

@@note For the following sections, we need to have a GitHub account. So check *here>https://services.github.com/on-demand/intro-to-github/create-github-account* if you do not have a GitHub account.
